article.description: — Dylan Painter posted 17 points as Delaware topped Fordham 81-71 in the Gulf Coast Showcase on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Painter scores 17 to lead Delaware over Fordham 81-71
article.linkText: Painter scores 17 to lead Delaware over Fordham 81-71
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- — Dylan Painter posted 17 points as Delaware topped Fordham 81-71 in the Gulf Coast Showcase on Tuesday night. Jameer Nelson Jr. had 15 points for Delaware (4-1), which won its fourth straight game. Kevin Anderson added 11 points. Andrew Carr had seven rebounds. Antonio Daye Jr. had 15 points for the Rams (3-3). Chuba Ohams added 12 points and eight rebounds. Darius Quisenberry had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
